<li><a href="http://www.gristmagazine.com/grist/books/lomborg121201.asp" class="external text" title="http://www.gristmagazine.com/grist/books/lomborg121201.asp" rel="nofollow">"Something Is Rotten in the State of Denmark"</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Grist" title="Grist">Grist</a> Magazine</i>, <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2001-12-12"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="12-12"><a href="/wiki/December_12" title="December 12">December 12</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2001" title="2001">2001</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=000F3D47-C6D2-1CEB-93F6809EC5880000" class="external text" title="http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=000F3D47-C6D2-1CEB-93F6809EC5880000" rel="nofollow">Misleading Math about the Earth: Science defends itself against The Skeptical Environmentalist</a> <i><a href="/wiki/Scientific_American" title="Scientific American">Scientific American</a></i> January 2002</li>
<li><a href="http://books.guardian.co.uk/reviews/scienceandnature/0,6121,544861,00.html" class="external text" title="http://books.guardian.co.uk/reviews/scienceandnature/0,6121,544861,00.html" rel="nofollow">Chris Lavers: "You've never had it so good"</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/The_Guardian" title="The Guardian">The Guardian</a></i> <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2001-09-01"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="09-01"><a href="/wiki/September_1" title="September 1">September 1</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2001" title="2001">2001</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
